		<p><b>Faction Hits:</b></font>
		<font color="#9f3215" face="verdana" size="2">
		<u><b>Worse</b></u><br></font>
		<font face="verdana" size="1" color="black">
		None<br>
		<br>
		<font color="#9f3215" face="verdana" size="2">
		<u><b>Better</b></u><br></font><font face="verdana" size="1" color="black">
		None<br>
		<br>
		</p></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan="3" width="585"><p align="center">
    <font color="#9f3215" face="verdana" size="2">This is a tougher type of undead.  It is found in many zones and has, by default, a rather unique ability for a monster.  Sometimes when hit by one of these, you'll be rooted in place.  It is identical to the root spell, except it's not a magic spell.  Make sure you can melee or dodge fairly well if you decide to solo these.  They are also immune to non-magical weapons.  Take note of this, and if you have no magical attack whatsoever, run.  Magic users, make sure you have a tank of some kind.  They are good experience, and carry good loot.</font></td>
  </tr>
</table><br>
