		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			Today, while bashing ghouls in the corner of Western Karana, my small party (19 Druid, 17 Paladin) was jumped by a Ghoul Messenger.  I had picked this badboy up on the Sense Undead radar earlier and it con'd red to me.  Our party was jumped while we were med'ing up and the Ghoul Messenger brought along a friend, Werewolf.  Both of us had SoW on for the quick-and-easy escape to the zone line into Northern Karana that was only a short distance away.  I (the paladin) just had to sit there as the GhoulRoot took away my SoW and the Ghoul Messenger beat me silly.  I had to use Lay Hands very soon and before the health bar could display my new HP, I was already below half.  This thing hit hard and brutal.  I briefly recall seeing damage counts of at least 59hp.<BR>
<BR>
We are wondering if this Ghoul Messenger is something similar to the Minotaur Hero in that after a certain condition is met, it starts cleaning house on the zone.  I can't think of any reason why this creature and his buddy traveled so far to beat me down.. unless he had a &quot;Sense Paladin&quot; spell and wanted the experience.  =)<BR>
<BR>
So beware.  This Ghoul Messenger con'd red to the L19 Druid.
			</font>
	
		</td>
